				<text type="text" lang="en">THE GIFT OF TONGUES</text>
			</inscription>
			<inscription>
				<author/>
				<position/>
				<text type="text" lang="en">Type is "the voice of the prinzed page," and a fine type face, of "single-type beauty," is like an attractive speaker with a good pleasent accent. This machine - a "MONOTYPE" machine - has the Gift of Tongues. Whatever language it is composing, from Icelandic to Tamil, will be made to look as attractive as a pleasent voice sounds - because SINGLE TYPE enhances its appearance. All over the world, printers use "MONOTYPE" machines to save composition and correction costs, increaase speed and get better results. (gs)</text>
